<div class="site_message">
  <h1>An error has occurred</h1>
  <% now = Time.now %>

  <div class="highlight"><div class="time_and_pre_msg">
    <p style="font-size:80%"><%= now.to_s %>:</p>
    <% if @exception %>
      <pre><%= @exception.message.gsub("#{Rails.root}/",'') %></pre>
    <% else %>
      <%# should probably never get here.. %>
      <pre>Can't see exception details</pre>
    <% end %>
  </div></div>

  <p>
    The Errata Tool dev team has been informed of this error via an email containing a stack trace and a
    dump of the request details, session data, and environment.
  </p>

  <p>If you would like to inquire about this issue or provide further information, consider the following actions:</p>
  <ul>
    <%# NB if you update this, you probably should update public/500.html also %>
    <li>Ask about it in #errata on IRC.</li>
    <li>Send an email to <a href="mailto:errata-dev-list@redhat.com">errata-dev-list@redhat.com</a>.</li>
    <li>Create an RT ticket by emailing <%= mail_to Settings.errata_help_email %>.</li>
    <li><a href="https://bugzilla.redhat.com/enter_bug.cgi?product=Errata%20Tool">Create a bug in Bugzilla</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Thank you for your patience.</p>
</div>
